FL,315,300,200,140,000,100
PN,31402
SC,0002
CT,2,C
PS,c008
OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F314A1782011884
OL,3,CHeatwave threshold likely met at
OL,4,Cweekend before next week's extreme
OL,5,Cheat warning
OL,7,FIt flags potential health impacts for
OL,8,Fpeople vulnerable to extreme heat and
OL,9,Fheat-related issues for the wider
OL,10,Fpopulation, as well as a potential
OL,11,Fincrease in water safety incidents.
OL,13,FThe warning, which differs from amber
OL,14,Fheat health alerts issued by the UK
OL,15,FHealth Security Agency (UKHSA), comes
OL,16,Fas another heatwave is expected to
OL,17,Fsweep parts of the UK during the
OL,18,Fweekend and early next week.
OL,1,W~k4~sj5j5~s1G                    G2/8
OL,2,W/*%+,"-/.!,.!T,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,
OL,23,TppppppppppppppppppGsource: itv.com/news
OL,24,ANext Page BNat News CNat TV FClean Feed
FL,315,300,200,140,000,100
PN,31403
SC,0003
CT,2,C
PS,c008
OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F314A1782011884
OL,3,CHeatwave threshold likely met at
OL,4,Cweekend before next week's extreme
OL,5,Cheat warning
OL,7,FAreas in southern and eastern England
OL,8,Fare likely to meet the heatwave
OL,9,Fthreshold during the weekend, and
OL,10,Fthere is a 40% chance of exceeding the
OL,11,Fhighest-ever temperature for June,
OL,12,Fwhich is 35.6C set in 1957 and 1976,
OL,13,Fthe Met Office said.
OL,15,FSaturday has a potential high of 28C
OL,16,Fbefore temperatures rise again from
OL,17,FSunday.
OL,1,W~k4~sj5j5~s1G                    G3/8
OL,2,W/*%+,"-/.!,.!T,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,
OL,23,TppppppppppppppppppGsource: itv.com/news
OL,24,ANext Page BNat News CNat TV FClean Feed
FL,315,300,200,140,000,100
PN,31404
SC,0004
CT,2,C
PS,c008
OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F314A1782011884
OL,3,CHeatwave threshold likely met at
OL,4,Cweekend before next week's extreme
OL,5,Cheat warning
OL,7,FSome areas in the south and south-east
OL,8,Fof England are forecast to reach 32C
OL,9,Fon that day and then push up or above
OL,10,F34C on Monday.
OL,12,FThey are again likely to reach the mid-
OL,13,F30s on Tuesday.
OL,15,FSome locations may see temperatures
OL,16,Fremain above 20C overnight on Monday
OL,17,Fand Tuesday, particularly in urban
OL,18,Fareas.
OL,1,W~k4~sj5j5~s1G                    G4/8
OL,2,W/*%+,"-/.!,.!T,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,
OL,23,TppppppppppppppppppGsource: itv.com/news
