FL,315,300,200,140,000,100
PN,31405
SC,0005
CT,2,C
PS,c008
OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F314A1782011884
OL,3,CHeatwave threshold likely met at
OL,4,Cweekend before next week's extreme
OL,5,Cheat warning
OL,7,FAmber heat health alerts are in force
OL,8,Fby the UKHSA for the east, south-east
OL,9,Fand south-west of England, as well as
OL,10,FLondon, until 8pm on Tuesday.
OL,12,FGreg Wolverson, deputy chief
OL,13,Fforecaster at the Met Office, said:
OL,14,F"While heatwave criteria will be met
OL,15,Ffor some in the south and south-east
OL,16,Fof England over the weekend, with
OL,17,Ftemperatures into the low 30s
OL,18,Fpossible, the warmth will expand and
OL,19,Fintensify at the start of next week,
OL,20,Fwhich, coupled with high temperatures
OL,21,Fovernight, leads to potential impacts.
OL,26,@vD@AOU
OL,1,W~k4~sj5j5~s1G                    G5/8
OL,2,W/*%+,"-/.!,.!T,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,
OL,23,TppppppppppppppppppGsource: itv.com/news
OL,24,ANext Page BNat News CNat TV FClean Feed
FL,315,300,200,140,000,100
PN,31406
SC,0006
CT,2,C
PS,c008
OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F314A1782011884
OL,3,CHeatwave threshold likely met at
OL,4,Cweekend before next week's extreme
OL,5,Cheat warning
OL,7,F"Temperatures will peak around the mid-
OL,8,F30s on Monday and Tuesday. The
OL,9,Fhumidity will also mean this feels
OL,10,Fclose, warmer and more uncomfortable
OL,11,Ffor many.
OL,13,F"Tropical nights ` where the
OL,14,Ftemperature doesn't drop below 20C `
OL,15,Fare also likely for some."
OL,17,FThe warmth may bring some thundery
OL,18,Fdownpours for some on Monday and
OL,19,FTuesday, though these should be
OL,20,F"fairly isolated", the Met Office said.
OL,26,@oD@AOUuD@AOUwD@ZO]|D@AOU|D@QO]
OL,1,W~k4~sj5j5~s1G                    G6/8
OL,2,W/*%+,"-/.!,.!T,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,
OL,23,TppppppppppppppppppGsource: itv.com/news
OL,24,ANext Page BNat News CNat TV FClean Feed
FL,315,300,200,140,000,100
PN,31407
SC,0007
CT,2,C
PS,c008
OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F314A1782011884
OL,3,CHeatwave threshold likely met at
OL,4,Cweekend before next week's extreme
OL,5,Cheat warning
OL,7,FThe very high temperatures could
OL,8,Fcontinue across a smaller part of the
OL,9,Fcountry into the middle of the week,
OL,10,Fbut this remains uncertain for now,
OL,11,Fthe forecaster added.
OL,13,FAt least 15 people died after getting
OL,14,Finto trouble in open water during a
OL,15,Fhot spell in May.
OL,17,FSamantha Hughes, national water safety
OL,18,Fpartner at the Royal National Lifeboat
OL,19,FInstitution, said: "With warmer
OL,20,Fweather approaching, it's important to
OL,21,Fremember that the water is still cold.
OL,26,@{D@TOU
OL,1,W~k4~sj5j5~s1G                    G7/8
OL,2,W/*%+,"-/.!,.!T,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,
